    "tags": ["GEN-1 robotics", "NVIDIA physical AI", "Claude for Word", "GLM-5.1", "GPT-5.5 Spud"],
    "fresh": true,
    "content": "**AI & Robotics Snacks** — April 12, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 🤖 GEN-1 Just Jumped From 64% to 99% Success Rate and Nobody Seems Alarmed\n\nGeneralist AI released GEN-1, an embodied foundation model that goes 3× faster than its predecessor and hits 99% success rates on real-world robotic tasks — up from 64%.\n\n- **The model:** Trained on large-scale real-world interaction data (not task-specific scripts), GEN-1 perceives, reasons, and acts in physical environments. The benchmark jump from 64% to 99% is not a typo.\n- **The framing:** \"Embodied foundation model\" is the new phrase. The idea is a general-purpose robot brain, trained the same way language models were trained — at scale.\n\n*From 64% to 99% in one generation. The previous generation is now just called the old one.*\n\n**Sources:** [Robotics & Automation News](https://roboticsandautomationnews.com/2026/04/11/generalist-ai-unveils-gen-1-model-claiming-breakthrough-in-real-world-robotic-task-performance/100516/)\n\n---\n\n## 🏭 NVIDIA Says the ChatGPT Moment for Robotics Is Here. Jensen Huang Says It Every Year. But This Time...\n\nNVIDIA announced Cosmos and GR00T open models, Isaac Lab-Arena evaluation, and the Jetson Thor platform for real-time humanoid robotics workloads.\n\n- **Jensen Huang's quote:** \"The ChatGPT moment for robotics is here. Breakthroughs in physical AI — models that understand the real world, reason and plan actions — are unlocking entirely new applications.\"\n- **What's real:** The Jetson Thor platform is shipping hardware for humanoid robots. Cosmos trains physical AI in simulation. GR00T is open-weighted. This is not a roadmap slide.\n\n*Jensen Huang has been announcing the ChatGPT moment for robotics for two years. He might be right by now.*\n\n**Sources:** [NVIDIA Newsroom](https://nvidianews.nvidia.com/news/nvidia-releases-new-physical-ai-models-as-global-partners-unveil-next-generation-robots) | [NVIDIA Blog](https://blogs.nvidia.com/blog/national-robotics-week-2026/)\n\n---\n\n## 📝 Anthropic Moved Into Microsoft Word and Microsoft Is Fine With It\n\nAnthropic launched Claude for Word — a direct add-in bringing AI-native drafting, tracked changes, and comment workflows into Microsoft's flagship document editor.\n\n- **The integration:** Organizations enabling the Anthropic connector get Claude as an alternative to GPT-4o in Copilot (Wave 3). A \"Researcher Council\" feature drafts with GPT then has Claude review for accuracy.\n- **The implication:** Microsoft is now shipping a competitor to its own AI (GPT-4o via Copilot) inside its own product. This is either very open-minded or GPT-4o is losing document tasks on merit.\n\n*Microsoft is the world's most valuable company and it just installed its competitor inside its flagship product. No notes.*\n\n**Sources:** [Irys AI](https://www.irys.ai/insights/market/claude-microsoft-365-copilot-word-integration-april-2026)\n\n---\n\n## 🌐 Z.ai's GLM-5.1 Is #1 Open Source and Nobody in the US Is Talking About It\n\nZ.ai released GLM-5.1, which hit #1 in open-source benchmarks and #3 globally — and can run autonomously for 8 hours.\n\n- **The model:** GLM-5.1 tops open-source performance benchmarks and sits third globally across multiple evaluations. The 8-hour autonomous operation is designed for extended agentic workflows.\n- **The context:** A Chinese AI lab is now beating every open-source model from Western labs. The narrative of US AI dominance is doing a lot of work right now.\n\n*Number one in open source. Built in China. The geopolitics of this sentence are left as an exercise for the reader.*\n\n**Sources:** [AI Updates Today](https://llm-stats.com/llm-updates) | [AI Model Releases April 2026](https://renovateqr.com/blog/ai-models-april-2026)\n\n---\n\n## 🥔 GPT-5.5 \"Spud\" Finished Training and OpenAI Is Saying Nothing\n\nOpenAI's GPT-5.5, codenamed Spud, completed pretraining around March 24 — and OpenAI has not announced a release date, or anything, publicly.\n\n- **The status:** Pretraining complete. Release date: unknown. Public acknowledgment: none. This is a model that exists and also does not exist, in the tradition of corporate AI launches.\n- **The context:** OpenAI just launched a new ChatGPT Pro tier to compete with Claude Code. GPT-5.4 is still the production model. Spud is in the drawer.\n\n*There's a finished AI model sitting in a drawer somewhere in San Francisco and its name is Spud.*\n\n**Sources:** [AI Model Releases April 2026](https://renovateqr.com/blog/ai-models-april-2026) | [CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/04/09/openai-chatgpt-pro-subscription-anthropic-claude-code.html)"
  }
]
